---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Build. Two Seven Builders"
  description="Built to be kept. Uncompromising framing, envelope, mechanical, and finish work for custom homes in the Ottawa Valley."
  active="build"
>
  <section class="hero" style="height:90vh;">
    <div class="hero-bg" style="background-image:url('/images/owner-lifting-beam.webp'); filter: brightness(0.78);"></div>
    <div class="hero-content">
      <span class="eyebrow fade-up">Build</span>
      <h1 class="serif fade-up d-1" style="margin-top:18px;">Built once.<br /><em>Built to be kept.</em></h1>
      <p class="hero-sub fade-up d-3" style="margin-top:32px;">No squeaks. No callbacks. No compromises.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-scroll">Scroll</div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap-narrow">
      <div class="reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow">What we mean by built</span>
        <h2 class="serif" style="margin:24px 0 36px;">The work disappears<br />into the walls.</h2>
        <p class="muted" style="font-size:clamp(18px, 1.4vw, 22px); line-height:1.55;">
          A great build is invisible. The fasteners are right. The flashing laps the right way. The studs are plumb on a Tuesday in February as well as on a Friday in July. None of this is photogenic, and all of it is why the house will be standing, square, and quiet, forty years from now.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="wrap">
    <div class="hp-row reveal">
      <div class="hp-text">
        <span class="num">01. Site &amp; Foundation</span>
        <h3 class="serif">Below grade, decided properly.</h3>
        <p>Drainage routed before backfill. Footings sized for the Valley's clay. Damp-proofing taped, not painted. The dirt gets attention because it's the only part of the house that can't be repaired without breaking the rest.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hp-img" data-parallax="0.08" style="background-image:url('/images/foundation-pre-build.webp')"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="hp-row reveal">
      <div class="hp-text">
        <span class="num">02. Framing &amp; Structure</span>
        <h3 class="serif">The bones, set true.</h3>
        <p>Engineered floors that don't bounce. Sealed sub-floors that don't squeak. Trusses raised on a clear morning by people who've raised a thousand. Every fastener placed on a schedule, every plate checked.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hp-img" data-parallax="0.08" style="background-image:url('/images/truss-day.webp')"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="hp-row reveal">
      <div class="hp-text">
        <span class="num">03. Envelope</span>
        <h3 class="serif">Tight. Then breathing.</h3>
        <p>Continuous air barrier, dense-pack cellulose, exterior rigid, a window package that won't surrender on a January morning. Blower-door tested before drywall, not at handoff, because finding a leak in winter is finding it too late.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hp-img" data-parallax="0.08" style="background-image:url('/images/framed-with-windows.webp')"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="hp-row reveal">
      <div class="hp-text">
        <span class="num">04. Mechanical &amp; Finish</span>
        <h3 class="serif">Quiet systems. Honest finishes.</h3>
        <p>HRV ventilation, in-floor radiant where it earns its keep, lighting circuits planned room by room. Trim that meets without caulk lines. Cabinetry that closes flush in a heat wave. The details are where the house is.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hp-img" data-parallax="0.08" style="background-image:url('/images/attention-to-detail-3.webp')"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="hp-row reveal">
      <div class="hp-text">
        <span class="num">05. Walkthrough &amp; After</span>
        <h3 class="serif">We don't disappear with the dumpster.</h3>
        <p>Final walkthrough. Deficiency resolution. A binder thicker than the warranty: every test, every change order, every spec. And a phone number that still answers in year ten.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hp-img" data-parallax="0.08" style="background-image:url('/images/finished-house-night-drop.webp')"></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bone">
    <div class="wrap" style="text-align:center;">
      <h2 class="serif split-text" style="max-width:24ch; margin:0 auto;">A house that outlives <em>the people who built it.</em></h2>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn" style="margin-top:48px;">Start the Process <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
